Global corn production will be 932.11
million metric tons in the year starting July 1, Informa
Economics Inc. said today in a report to clients.  Last month, the Memphis, Tennessee-based agricultural
researcher forecast output at 918.599 million tons, up from an
estimated 868.017 million harvested in the current year. The
U.S. Department of Agriculture is scheduled to make its first
